 The
Faku family is in pain after Richard Jabulile Faku, aged 74 went missing. He
was last seen on 24 December. A
case of missing persons was opened at Daveyton police station. Her daughter
Thembisile Faku said she left for work in the morning and when she returned,
her father was nowhere to be found. Mkhulu Faku takes various medications and
he has not been able to do so since his disappearance. You must be SIGNED IN to read comments On
the day he disappeared, he was wearing black T-shirt with red stripes and a
short with white stripe and brown sandals. Anyone who sees him is urged to
contact his daughter Thembisile on 0764116802. 